SALMONELLA AGONA, FOODBORNE DISEASE - USA (02)
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Salmonella agona, foodborne disease - USA 980604225415
[1
Date: 5 Jun 1998 01:55:14 -0000
From: Brent Barrett <salbrent@iquest.net>

During April - May 1998, 11 states reported an increase in Salmonella
serotype Agona cases to CDC. As of June 4, 1998, 188 cases have been
reported and 40 persons were hospitalized. Cases have been reported from
Illinois (46), Indiana (29), Michigan (15), Ohio (21), Missouri (18), New
York (22), Pennsylvania (20), Iowa (7), Kansas (3), West Virginia (2), and
Wisconsin (5). No deaths have been reported.
With coordination from CDC, a case-control study was conducted by state
health departments from involved states to identify common source
exposures. Consumption of Millville brand Toasted Oats cereal, distributed
by Aldi's supermarkets in the aforementioned states, is associated with
these cases of S. Agona infections in April- May 1998.
--
Brent Barrett,
Indiana State Dept of Health,
e-mail: salbrent@iquest.net
[Thanks Brent for forwarding this material from a CDC press release. I
have cut some part of the press release we covered in our first posting.
However, I thought the geographic distribution might be of interest to some
of our readers and it's always good to know a case control study has been
completed. - Mod.PC
